<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-04-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-04-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="397" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d397">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Breckinridge</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-04-17"><hi rend="italic">April 17,
                                1896</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 223.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            No. 271 of the 1st instant, inclosing copy of your note to the Russian
                            minister of foreign affairs in the matter of the citizens of the United
                            States said to have been imprisoned at Saghalien on the charge of
                            illegal sealing.</p>
                        <p>Your note is approved.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>